
[1]lazy

   LA'ZY, a. [L. laxus, and it is doubtful whether this is of the same
   family.]

   1. Disinclined to action or exertion; naturally or habitually slothful;
   sluggish; indolent; averse to labor; heavy in motion.

   Wicked men will ever live like rogues, and not fall to work, but be
   lazy and spend victuals.

   2. Slow; moving slowly or apparently with labor; as a lazy stream.

   The night-owl's lazy flight.
